===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈskɛə.krəʊ/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈsker.kroʊ/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[effigy]], typically made of [[straw]] and dressed in old clothes, fixed to a [[pole]] in a field to [[deter]] [[bird]]s from [[eating]] [[seed]]s or [[crop]]s planted there.
# {{context|figuratively|pejorative|lang=en}} A [[tall]], [[thin]], [[awkward]] person.
# {{context|figurative|lang=en}} Anything that appears [[terrifying]] but offers no [[danger]].
#: ''A '''scarecrow''' set to frighten fools away.'' &mdash; Dryden.
# A person clad in [[rag]]s and [[tatter]]s.
#: ''No eye hath seen such '''scarecrows'''. I'll not march with them through Coventry, that's flat.'' &mdash; Shakespeare.
# {{context|UK|dialect|lang=en}} A bird, the [[black tern]].

